The paper deals with algorithms for distance computation and subgraph detection tasks, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of algebraic methods and matrix multiplication algorithms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of all-pairs shortest paths and girth computation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
